title.narrative: MENTAL HEALTH AND SCHOOL-BASED NUTRITION

description.narrative: By 2025 appropriate models of adolescents' mental health and school-based nutrition services are piloted, evaluated and costed for further replication at national level., which contributes to Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement (Covid), Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2025 designated government agencies have increased capacity to collect, analyze and use data to inform decision-making, and have strengthened capacity to address mother and child health, development and environmental health needs.

description.narrative: UNICEF contributed to the Government agreement on improving infant and young child feeding across the country, including the Prime Minister’s engagement in the introduction of the School Nutrition Programme.;UNICEF equipped 1,600 grade 8 - 10 students with knowledge on simple mechanisms for emotional regulations and stress management triggering an expanded partnership with the Ministry of Education and Science to address socio-emotional learning at school.UNICEF research showed low knowledge amongst adolescents on gambling risks and reached 1,100 adolescents reached with gambling prevention information. | Status:Met | As-of Date:20/01/2022
